      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "James, please don't apologize. It took real courage to tell me this, and I'm glad you did.\n\nWhat you're describing — pain bad enough to stop you mid-run, three times in a row — that's your body sending a clear signal, and it deserves to be taken seriously. The fact that you kept going while dealing with that tells me how much this running matters to you. That's not something to be ashamed of. It's actually something worth understanding.\n\nHere's where I have to be straight with you, because I care about getting this right: **diagnosing what's happening with your foot and telling you how to treat it is genuinely outside what I can do for you.** I'm your running coach, not a medical professional — and with foot pain that's gotten worse despite rest and caution, you need someone who can actually examine you. That means going back to your physiotherapist, ideally soon. If the pain was stopping you mid-run, this warrants a conversation with them before you lace up again.\n\nWhat I *can* do — and will do the moment you have updated guidance from them — is rebuild your plan around whatever they clear you for. We had a solid, conservative foundation in place. That foundation doesn't disappear; it just gets paused while you get the right information.\n\n**One thing I'd ask you to do this week:** Contact your physio and let them know what's changed — specifically that the pain increased and you had to stop three runs early. They need that full picture to give you good guidance.\n\nWhile you're waiting for that appointment, can I ask — what's been the hardest part of all this? I want to make sure we're building something sustainable when you come back, not just physically but in terms of what actually works for your life."
        }
      ],
      "messageId": "msg_01AKwKzGny2rTvUZvTYMcwjs"
    }
